      <prompt>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <div>
              <p>A 36-year-old woman is started on trimethoprim for a urinary tract infection. Routine blood tests 2 days later reveal the following:</p>
              <p>Sodium    135 mmol/L (normal range 135–145 mmol/L)</p>
              <p>Potassium        6.4 mmol/L (normal range 3.3–4.7 mmol/L)</p>
              <p>Urea        6.4 mmol/L (normal range 2.5–6.6 mmol/L)</p>
              <p>Creatinine 125 μmol/L (normal range 60–120 μmol/L)</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div>
              <p>A 26-year-old woman presents with fatigue and feeling generally out of sorts. On examination she is clinically dehydrated with a postural drop in her blood pressure. Her blood tests are below:</p>
              <p>Sodium    135 mmol/ L (normal range 135–145 mmol/L)</p>
              <p>Potassium        6.5 mmol/ L (normal range 3.3–4.7 mmol/L)</p>
              <p>Urea        8.4 mmol/L (normal range 2.5–6.6 mmol/L)</p>
              <p>Creatinine 96 μmol/L (normal range 60–120 μmol/L)</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div>
              <p>An 28-year-old woman is admitted with community acquired pneumonia. On arrival she is tachycardic at 140/min with a blood pressure of 95/60 mmHg. Blood tests show:</p>
              <p>Sodium    135 mmol/L (normal range 135–145 mmol/L)</p>
              <p>Potassium        7.2 mmol/L (normal range 3.3–4.7 mmol/L)</p>
              <p>Urea        20.2 mmol/L (normal range 2.5–6.6 mmol/L)</p>
              <p>Creatinine 200 μmol/L (normal range 60–120 μmol/L)</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div>
              <p>A 25-year-old is admitted with a 2-day history of dry cough and fever. The CXR shows right lower lobe consolidation. Blood tests show:</p>
              <p>Sodium    145 mmol/L (normal range 135–145 mmol/L)</p>
              <p>Potassium        6.8 mmol/L (normal range 3.3–4.7 mmol/L)</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ol>
