  <modalFeedback identifier="CORRECT_FEEDBACK" outcomeIdentifier="GENERAL_FEEDBACK" showHide="show">
    <p>
      <b>Option I (Type 4 renal tubular acidosis) is Correct.</b>
      Type 4 renal tubular acidosis or aldosterone resistance is suggested by hyperkalaemia and slightly impaired renal function. It may be caused by a number of drugs including trimethoprim and spironolactone.
    </p>
  </modalFeedback>
